        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued November 23 at 8:03PM CST by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 803 PM CST, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
The Intersection Of Highway 158 And Ranch Road 2059, or near E.V.
Spence Reservoir Near Paint Creek Recreation Area, moving east at 25
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Winters, Robert Lee, Blackwell, Bronte, Hylton, E.V. Spence Reservoir
Near Paint Creek Recreation Area, Wingate, Happy Valley, Fort
Chadbourne, Sanco, Shep, Wilmeth, Pumphrey, The Intersection Of
Highway 158 And Ranch Road 2059, and Oak Creek Reservoir.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM CST for
west central Texas.</instruction>
